HEADWORD: Labialism
<hw>La"bi*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Phonetics)</fld>
<def>The quality of being labial; <as>as, the <ex>labialism</ex> of an
articulation</as>; conversion into a labial, as of a sound which is
different in another language.</def> <rj><au>J. Peile.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labialization</ent>⟦br⟧
